PRE-REQUISITE: subscription_status=TRIAL, trial_ends_at 2 days from now.

SQL: UPDATE "Company" SET subscription_status='TRIAL', trial_ends_at=NOW() + INTERVAL '2 days' WHERE id='<id>';

UI CHECK: amber banner: 'Your free trial ends in 2 days. Subscribe soon to avoid losing edit access.'

PRE-REQUISITE: subscription_status=TRIAL, trial_ends_at = today (later today UTC).

SQL: UPDATE "Company" SET subscription_status='TRIAL', trial_ends_at=NOW() + INTERVAL '2 hours' WHERE id='<id>';

UI CHECK: red banner: 'Your free trial ends today. Subscribe to keep creating and editing work.'

PRE-REQUISITE: subscription_status still TRIAL but trial_ends_at is in the past (cron hasn't run yet or test scenario).

SQL: UPDATE "Company" SET subscription_status='TRIAL', trial_ends_at='2020-01-01' WHERE id='<id>';

UI CHECK: red banner: 'Your free trial has ended. Your account may be locked soon.' No lock yet — backend cron owns that.

PRE-REQUISITE: subscription_status=ACTIVE.

SQL: UPDATE "Company" SET subscription_status='ACTIVE' WHERE id='<id>';

UI CHECK: No trial banner visible anywhere in the dashboard.

PRE-REQUISITE: subscription_status=LOCKED.

SQL: UPDATE "Company" SET subscription_status='LOCKED' WHERE id='<id>';

UI CHECK: No trial banner in header. The LockedOverlay modal fires when any write attempt returns 403 with code=SUBSCRIPTION_LOCKED.
